Class Resource

java.lang.Object
app.tracktune.model.resource.Resource
Direct Known Subclasses:
MultimediaResource
public class Resource extends Object
Represents a general resource entity associated with a track and a user. This class stores metadata and binary data for a resource, which can be multimedia or other types.

  • Constructor Details

    • Resource

      public Resource(Integer id, ResourceTypeEnum type, byte[] data, Timestamp creationDate, boolean isMultimedia, boolean isAuthor, int trackID, int userID)
      Constructs a Resource with the specified fields including an explicit ID.
      Parameters:
      id - the unique identifier of the resource, may be null if not assigned yet
      type - the type of the resource (see ResourceTypeEnum)
      data - the binary content of the resource
      creationDate - the timestamp when the resource was created
      isMultimedia - true if the resource is multimedia, false otherwise
      isAuthor - true if the resource is related to an author, false otherwise
      trackID - the identifier of the track this resource is linked to
      userID - the identifier of the user who owns or created the resource

    • Resource

      public Resource(ResourceTypeEnum type, byte[] data, Timestamp creationDate, boolean isMultimedia, boolean isAuthor, int trackID, int userID)
      Constructs a Resource without specifying an ID (e.g., for new resources before database insertion).
      Parameters:
      type - the type of the resource (see ResourceTypeEnum)
      data - the binary content of the resource
      creationDate - the timestamp when the resource was created
      isMultimedia - true if the resource is multimedia, false otherwise
      isAuthor - true if the resource is related to an author, false otherwise
      trackID - the identifier of the track this resource is linked to
      userID - the identifier of the user who owns or created the resource
